{
  "texts": [
    "The integrity feature ensures only authorized users can modify IoT device information when utilizing wireless communication networks [110].",
    "Weaknesses in integrity checks can open the door to data tampering within IoT device memory, potentially jeopardizing the core functionality of physical devices and persisting undetected for extended periods.",
    "Solutions for ensuring integrity in IoT encompass the generation or utilization of data through programmed methods [108].or specialized DDoS mitigation services to absorb and reduce the high volume of malicious traffic generated by the attack.",
    "In addition, IoT devices must be regularly patched and updated to reduce their susceptibility to becoming part of a botnet used in DDoS attacks [95].• Malware and RansomwareRansomware is malicious software restricting access to critical data and demanding payment for its release.",
    "In this attack, the offender seeks to encrypt the victim's data using robust encryption techniques and requests a ransom, typically in Bitcoin, in exchange for the decryption key."
  ]
}